		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=32894"><span id=>Vyzare</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>4 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Vyzare&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Ok I won't say there's a best race for a warrior as there are just so many races that can be a warrior.&nbsp;&nbsp;I'll instead list some of the pros and cons of each one.<br><br>Barbarian - Have a choice between large and medium armor.  Have the ability to slam while using a 2hander or dual wielding and Don't have many faction problems.  However they are also blind as a bat when night falls.<br><br>Dark Elf - Have a choice between small and medium armor.  Have very nice agi.  Look very cool in plate armor.  However they are fairly weak, they're dex isn't as good as wood elves.  Oh, dark elves also have ultravision so you won't even know if it's night or not.<br><br>Dwarf - Have very good all around warrior stats.  Good str, good sta, good dex.  A little lacking in the agi department, but that can be fixed.  Can only wear small armor.<br><br>Gnome - Lower than a dwarf in all physicals except agil.  Good int if you want to play with trade skills.  Can only wear small armor.<br><br>Half Elf - Well round stats for a warrior.  Good dex for critical hits and proccing weapons.  Look nifty in plate armor too.  Can only wear medium armor.<br><br>Halfling - Great dex (same as a dwarf).  Great Agil.  Fair str and sta.  Racial hide and sneak skills.  Can only wear small armor.<br><br>Human - Average stats, no special racial skills, blind as a bat.  Can only wear medium armor.<br><br>Iksar - Average Str and Sta, High dex and agi.  Natural ac bonus, natural regen.  Inability to wear most pieces of plate armor, KoS everywhere outside their home city. Can only wear medium armor.  Also start with master swimming and racial forage.<br><br>Ogre - Highest str and sta in the game.  Fairly low agi and dex.  Have the ability to slam like barbarians.  An evil race, KoS in most good cities.  Can only wear large armor.<br><br>Troll - Good str and sta.  Decent agi and dex.  Natural regeneration.  Probably the most popular warrior race in the game (both a pro and a con).  Abilitiy to slam like Barbs and Ogres.  Also an evil race.  Can only wear large armor.<br><br>Wood Elf - Fair str, low sta.  High agi, moderate dex.  Can wear small and med armor.  Racial ability to hide and forage.<br><br>All in All there is no best race for the warrior.  Any of them can fare quite well as a warrior is determined by skill and equipment.  The slam skill is a nice addition as it allows you to dual wield or use a 2hander and still bash.  Dex and Agi are very important warrior stats as agi will help you avoid hits and dex will help you critical hit and proc weaponry.  Personally I play an iksar warrior, because with the addition of the new velious armor they will be very powerful at high levels, but I have a long time to wait until then =).<br><br>Vyzare - 21 DE SK Torvo<br>Xixlix - 13 Iks War Torvo<br><br></p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
